1
00:00:01,300 --> 00:00:03,580
要知道 犯罪生涯的阴暗面之一就是
You know, one of the downsides to a life of crime

2
00:00:03,580 --> 00:00:08,700
你必须时不时地同某些人打交道 唔...
is that occasionally you have to do business with people who are, um...

3
00:00:08,700 --> 00:00:12,380
嗯 说得好听点 罪犯们
Well, for want of a better word, criminals.

4
00:00:15,260 --> 00:00:19,180
像大多数不得善终的事情一样
Like most things that end with you hanging upside down

5
00:00:19,180 --> 00:00:21,060
即便你最终被倒吊在废弃的仓库里
in a deserted warehouse,

6
00:00:21,060 --> 00:00:24,380
刚开始它可的确是条妙计
it started with a really good idea.

7
00:00:24,380 --> 00:00:28,460
"《花园中的小猫》由巴勃罗・毕加索绘于1903年
"A Small Cat In The Garden was painted by Pablo Picasso in 1903,

8
00:00:28,460 --> 00:00:30,820
"这一时期被称之为他的蓝色时期
"in what was known as his Blue Period.

9
00:00:30,820 --> 00:00:34,940
"画的尺寸为12x11英寸 星期天的凌晨时分 
"It measures 12 inches by 11 inches and was stolen from a private collection

10
00:00:34,940 --> 00:00:37,220
"从私人藏品里偷取"
"in the early hours of Sunday morning."

11
00:00:37,220 --> 00:00:38,420
嗯...值多少?
Mmmm... Value?

12
00:00:38,420 --> 00:00:40,620
-投保金额有3百万  -哇奥
-It's been insured for three million.  -Wow.

13
00:00:40,620 --> 00:00:43,820
"警方说 盗窃团伙显然经验老道 消息灵通"
"Police say the gang was clearly experienced and well informed."

14
00:00:43,820 --> 00:00:46,340
-意思是偷这幅画是有的放矢  -这毫无疑问
-Meaning it was stolen to order.  -No question.

15
00:00:46,340 --> 00:00:50,660
-疯子Dolly还在附近吗?  -我也在想
-Is Mad Dolly still around?  -My thoughts exactly.

16
00:00:50,660 --> 00:00:51,310
谁?
Who?

17
00:00:51,310 --> 00:00:52,840
Dolly Hammond
Dolly Hammond,

18
00:00:52,850 --> 00:00:54,820
在伦敦 她仿造的毕加索作品是最逼真的
she's the best Picasso forger in London.

19
00:00:54,820 --> 00:00:57,660
她人不错 就是有一点...她...比较特立独行
She's all right, but she's just a bit.... She's...unique.

20
00:00:57,660 --> 00:00:59,740
是的 她是有点儿与众不同 这你懂
Yeah, she's a bit different, you know.

21
00:00:59,740 --> 00:01:00,780
-疯疯癫癫的  -对 没错
-Insane.  -Yeah. Nice.

22
00:01:00,780 --> 00:01:03,620
实际上她是个可爱的老精明鬼 但是 额...
She's a lovely old bird really, but, erm...

23
00:01:03,620 --> 00:01:05,540
她过去曾迷恋Albie
she used to have the hots for Albie.

24
00:01:05,540 --> 00:01:09,180
既然画已经被偷 为什么我们还要找人伪造它?
Why would we need someone to forge a painting that's already been stolen?

25
00:01:09,180 --> 00:01:11,980
恩 是因为现在失窃一事已经被报道了...
Well, because now its theft has already been reported...

26
00:01:11,980 --> 00:01:14,210
如果你告诉收藏家们你试图卖掉这幅画
Collectors will believe you

27
00:01:14,210 --> 00:01:15,460
他们会相信你的是真品
if you tell 'em you're trying to sell it.

28
00:01:15,460 --> 00:01:17,300
这主意棒极了!
It's brilliant!

29
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:19,860
-是的没错  -是的没错  -一向如此
-Yes, it is.  -Yes, it is.  -As always.

30
00:01:19,860 --> 00:01:22,020
呃 看起来棒极了
Well, potentially brilliant.

31
00:01:22,020 --> 00:01:25,020
这取决于你想把赝品卖给谁
Depending on who you try and sell the fake to.

32
00:01:26,260 --> 00:01:27,900
给你一个小忠告
And here's a little tip

33
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:32,020
如果你想非法销售毕加索的赝品...
should you ever find yourself trying to flog a fake Picasso...

34
00:01:36,380 --> 00:01:38,020
可别把它卖给
Don't try and sell it to the bloke

35
00:01:38,020 --> 00:01:40,620
真品最初的主人 画可是从那儿偷的
who the original was nicked from in the first place.

36
00:01:46,740 --> 00:01:51,620
好了好了 骑兵们来了
Aye-aye. Here come the cavalry.

37
00:01:51,620 --> 00:01:52,740
Ash!
Ash!

38
00:02:01,380 --> 00:02:02,940
轻点 Sean 轻点!
Gently, Sean, gently!

39
00:02:02,940 --> 00:02:04,340
噢...
Oooh...

40
00:02:12,660 --> 00:02:14,820
-Mickey在哪?  -他们拿枪对着我们呢
-Where's Mickey?  -They pulled a gun on us.

41
00:02:14,820 --> 00:02:16,730
Petre Sava的人抓了他
Petre Sava's men have taken him.

42
00:02:16,730 --> 00:02:17,340
发生什么了?
What happened?

43
00:02:17,340 --> 00:02:18,710
啊 说来话长
Well, it's a very long story,

44
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:22,060
但结果是真品一开始就从他那儿被偷了
but the upshot is the original was nicked from him in the first place.

45
00:02:22,060 --> 00:02:25,020
我们告诉他是我们偷了画
He wasn't happy at us telling him it was us who nicked it,

46
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:31,060
然后打算卖他幅假的来代替真的 他就怒了
and then trying to sell him a fake back instead of the real thing.

47
00:02:36,460 --> 00:02:39,420
这不是毕加索!
This is NOT Picasso!

48
00:02:39,420 --> 00:02:41,540
这不是我的画!
This is not my painting!

49
00:02:41,540 --> 00:02:43,450
所以在我们把真的毕加索还给他之前
So Petre Sava is holding on to Mickey

50
00:02:43,450 --> 00:02:45,940
Petre Sava是不会放了Mickey的
till we deliver the real Picasso back to him.

51
00:02:45,940 --> 00:02:47,290
我们又没有真品
We haven't got the real one.

52
00:02:47,290 --> 00:02:49,500
对 这一点我强调过了 为此我们还争了一会
No, I did mention that, and we argued for a bit,

53
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,780
然后他威胁会暴力相加
then he threatened a level of physical violence

54
00:02:51,780 --> 00:02:54,060
我对此很是不喜欢 所以放弃了
I wasn't comfortable with, so I backed down.

55
00:02:54,060 --> 00:02:56,340
他给我们6小时找到它
He's given us six hours to find it.

56
00:03:16,260 --> 00:03:19,340
如果我们找不到真画会怎样?
So what happens if we can't find the real painting?

57
00:03:19,340 --> 00:03:21,340
哦 这一点他说得特详细
Oh, he was very specific about that.

58
00:03:21,340 --> 00:03:23,260
Mickey必死无疑
Mickey's a dead man.

59
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:16,300

60
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:55,260
这么说没人发现任何线索?但这不可能
So no-one's got anything? But that's impossible.

61
00:04:55,260 --> 00:04:56,860
嗯 这不是当地团伙犯的案
Well, it's not a local crew.

62
00:04:56,860 --> 00:04:58,630
如果是的话 肯定有知情者
Someone would know if it was.

63
00:04:58,630 --> 00:05:01,420
目前真画很可能已经被运出国了
By now the real painting could've been shipped out of the country.

64
00:05:01,420 --> 00:05:03,950
但没人听到任何动静也太奇怪了
But it's weird that no-one's heard anything.

65
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:06,060
或者他们有 却不愿拿出来分享
Or if they have, they don't want to share it.

66
00:05:06,060 --> 00:05:07,710
Dolly仿造画的人那边呢?
What about that Dolly the forger?

67
00:05:07,710 --> 00:05:09,700
如果她是毕加索的狂热爱好者
If she's a Picasso freak,

68
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:11,260
她应该会听说点什么消息
she might have heard something.

69
00:05:11,260 --> 00:05:11,900
我想...
I suppose...

70
00:05:11,900 --> 00:05:15,300
-是啊 对 没错 能试试  -我们行动吧
-Yeah. Yeah, yeah, it's worth a try.  -Let's do it.

71
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:19,040
如今都找不到个有水准的大盗了
Can't find a decent thief these days,

72
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:21,980
全都是些匪徒 真上不了台面
they're all gangsters, they've got no class.

73
00:05:21,980 --> 00:05:25,780
-不像你 Albert  -谢谢你 Dolly
-Not like you Albert.  -Thank you, Dolly.

74
00:05:25,780 --> 00:05:28,740
我真想把他们用睾丸串起来
I'd string 'em all up. By the testicles.

75
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:32,740
丢出去让乌鸦啄
Leave them there for the crows to pick at.

76
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:37,780
剩下的就喂猪 像我们过去常做的那样
Feed what's left to the pigs, like we used to.

77
00:05:37,780 --> 00:05:40,340
Dolly 你知不知道是谁偷了那幅毕加索?
So you've no idea who stole the Picasso, Dolly?

78
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:42,660
-哪幅毕加索?  -《花园中的小猫》
-What Picasso?  -A Small Cat In The Garden.

79
00:05:42,660 --> 00:05:45,540
你的仿制品我已经画好给你了
You've had your copy, I've already done it.

80
00:05:45,540 --> 00:05:47,420
不不 我说的是那幅真品
No, no, I'm talking about the real one.

81
00:05:47,420 --> 00:05:49,660
他真可爱
He's cute.

82
00:05:50,740 --> 00:05:53,810
Dolly 那幅画 你知道是谁偷的吗?
Dolly, the painting, have you any idea who nicked it?

83
00:05:53,810 --> 00:05:55,020
这种事我怎么知道?
How would I know that?

84
00:05:55,020 --> 00:05:57,240
-有人跟你说过什么吗?  -谁?
-Has no-one said anything to you?  -Who?

85
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:58,660
-随便谁  -说什么?
-Anyone.  -Said what?

86
00:05:58,660 --> 00:06:00,460
-关于画的事  -什么画?
-About the painting.  -What painting?

87
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:02,690
-毕加索的画  -我不知道谁偷了它
-The Picasso.  -I don't know who nicked it.

88
00:06:02,690 --> 00:06:05,000
额 我就问这个 不是吗?
Well, that's what I'm asking, innit?

89
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,540
我已经告诉你了 你是谁?
I've told you. Who are you?

90
00:06:06,540 --> 00:06:07,580
哦...我是Emma
Oh... I'm Emma.

91
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:10,300
你在我家做什么?
What are you doing in my house?

92
00:06:10,300 --> 00:06:12,820
我和Albert一起的
I'm with Albert.

93
00:06:12,820 --> 00:06:15,180
她是你的小情妇 对吗?
This your floozy, is it?

94
00:06:15,180 --> 00:06:19,100
不不不不 Dolly 你是我唯一的女人
No, no, no, no. You're the only woman for me, Dolly.

95
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:21,500
噢!啊...不好意思啦
Ohhh! Aah...unlucky.

96
00:06:21,510 --> 00:06:24,780
Dolly 你对这幅画一点儿都不知情?
Dolly, do you know anything at all about the painting?

97
00:06:24,780 --> 00:06:27,340
任何能帮我们找到窃贼的线索都行
Anything that might help us find out who nicked it?

98
00:06:27,340 --> 00:06:31,260
我是说 有没有谁非常爱这幅画?私人收藏家?
I mean, was there someone who really liked it? A private collector?

99
00:06:31,260 --> 00:06:35,940
或者有谁之前想买却没买到手?任何相关的事都行
Or did someone try and buy it before and failed? Anything.

100
00:06:35,940 --> 00:06:38,460
我知道伦敦每一幅毕加索的藏地
I know where every Picasso in London is.

101
00:06:41,540 --> 00:06:43,260
我能嗅出来
I can smell them.

102
00:06:45,140 --> 00:06:46,500
除了这一幅
Except this one.

103
00:06:48,460 --> 00:06:51,460
Dolly 听着 你有什么办法找到它吗?
Dolly, look, is there any way you can track it down, you know?

104
00:06:51,460 --> 00:06:53,220
我是说 街头巷尾都流传些什么消息?
I mean, what's the word on the street?

105
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:54,900
我看上去像抱抱熊吗?
Do I look like Huggy Bear?

106
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:57,020
Dolly!我们需要找到它
Dolly! We need to find it.

107
00:06:58,340 --> 00:07:01,220
我会想想我能做些什么的 只要...
I'll see what I can do, if...

108
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:03,700
..他对我唱唱歌
..he sings to me,

109
00:07:03,700 --> 00:07:06,140
他亲亲我
and he snogs me.

110
00:07:07,180 --> 00:07:11,500
# 你好 Dolly 呀 你好 Dolly #
# Hello Dolly, well, Hello Dolly #

111
00:07:11,500 --> 00:07:16,100
# 你回来真好 回到你属于的地方! #
# It's so nice to have you back where you belong! #

112
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:20,540
哦...
Oh...

113
00:07:24,380 --> 00:07:25,460
不
No.

114
00:07:26,420 --> 00:07:29,790
算了吧 别... 别这样
Forget it. It's...it's not happening.

115
00:07:29,790 --> 00:07:32,100
Sean 想想Mickey
Sean, think about Mickey.

116
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:33,660
-别提Mickey  -亲一下吧
-Forget Mickey.  -Do it.

117
00:07:33,660 --> 00:07:34,540
我不想...做这事
I don't want to... Do it.

118
00:07:36,140 --> 00:07:37,940
-我不想!  -Sean...
-Don't want to!  -Sean...

119
00:07:57,860 --> 00:08:00,060
真顽皮!
Naughty!

120
00:08:04,980 --> 00:08:06,980
怎样?
Well?

121
00:08:06,980 --> 00:08:11,060
额...嗯 几个小时内我应该就能知道
Erm...well, I should know in a couple of hours.

122
00:08:11,060 --> 00:08:13,060
派他来
Send him.

123
00:08:49,660 --> 00:08:51,770
现在 以防Dolly想不出线索
Now, just in case Dolly draws a blank,

124
00:08:51,770 --> 00:08:53,100
我们最好全面行动起来
we'd better cover all the angles.

125
00:08:53,100 --> 00:08:54,620
Albert 同警方联络下
Albert, use your police contacts,

126
00:08:54,620 --> 00:08:56,140
看看他们那儿有什么线索
see if they've got any leads on the robbery

127
00:08:56,140 --> 00:08:58,380
-或者知道可能会是谁  -行
-or any idea who it was.  -Right.

128
00:08:58,380 --> 00:08:59,670
Sean 你开车 
Sean, take the car.

129
00:08:59,670 --> 00:09:02,620
看看能不能查到Petre Sava的其他信息
See what else you can find out about Petre Sava.

130
00:09:02,620 --> 00:09:02,740
好
OK.

131
00:09:03,820 --> 00:09:06,220
-我们干什么?  -你跟我去见Cyclops
-What about us?  -You and me will go and see Cyclops.

132
00:09:06,220 --> 00:09:08,480
虽然艺术品不是他的菜
Now, art's not really his thing,

133
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:10,100
但他也许会听到些消息
but he might have heard something.

134
00:09:17,740 --> 00:09:22,020
我有一幅《玩斯诺克的狗》可以吗?
I've got The Dogs Playing Snooker, if that's any good to you?

135
00:09:22,020 --> 00:09:24,420
那可是经典作品
It's a classic.

136
00:09:24,420 --> 00:09:27,860
我曾经有幅《在网球场上挠她屁股的鸟》
I used to have The Bird On The Tennis Court Scratching Her Bum,

137
00:09:27,860 --> 00:09:31,980
但它在家庭纠纷中被高跟鞋划坏了
but it got stiletto damage in a domestic dispute.

138
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:34,570
哎 女人并不懂艺术 没说错吧?
Well, women don't really get art, do they?

139
00:09:34,570 --> 00:09:35,260
是这样吗?
Is that right?

140
00:09:35,260 --> 00:09:37,820
没错 众所周知
Yeah, well-known fact.

141
00:09:37,820 --> 00:09:40,300
她们对艺术没有耐心
They've got no patience for it.

142
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:44,660
所以主流艺术家全是男性 女人从来都半途而废
That's why all the major artists are all men. Women would never be able to finish anything.

143
00:09:44,660 --> 00:09:47,300
《微笑骑士》欣赏到一半 
They'd be halfway through The Laughing Cavalier,

144
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:51,100
她们就走神了 开始分颜色整理鞋柜
then they'd wander off and start colour-coding their shoe cupboard.

145
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:53,020
听着 我们能回到当前的问题上吗?
Look, can we get back to the matter in hand?

146
00:09:53,020 --> 00:09:53,900
什么问题?
Which was?

147
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:55,900
《花园中的小猫》 那幅被偷了的毕加索
A Small Cat In The Garden. The stolen Picasso.

148
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:57,500
-哦 好  -谁偷的?
-Oh, yeah.  -So who nicked it?

149
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:59,280
艺术品不是我的菜
Art's not really my thing.

150
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:01,060
-我说过 是吧?  -是的
-I said that, didn't I?  -Yeah.

151
00:10:01,060 --> 00:10:02,420
-但我听说过它  -什么?
-But I heard about it.  -What?

152
00:10:02,420 --> 00:10:04,280
我说我听说过它
I said I heard about it.

153
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:06,660
不...不不 你听到什么了?
No...No, no, what did you hear?

154
00:10:08,180 --> 00:10:11,980
-听说它被偷了 来一片吗?  -不用了 谢谢
-That it was nicked. You want a chip?  -No. Thank you.

155
00:10:11,980 --> 00:10:14,780
-有时间约个会吗?  -没有
-Any chance of a date?  -None.

156
00:10:14,780 --> 00:10:17,760
同情的施舍呢? 把它看成慈善工作吧 就一会儿
Sympathy shag? Think of it as charity work, it's been a while.

157
00:10:17,760 --> 00:10:20,380
Cyclops 听着 Mickey有麻烦了
Look, Cyclops, Mickey's in trouble.

158
00:10:20,380 --> 00:10:22,740
不管你知道什么 你都要告诉我
Whatever you know, you need to tell me.

159
00:10:22,740 --> 00:10:25,500
-我们还没讲价呢  -什么?你还要对我们收钱?
-We haven't haggled yet.  -What? You're going to charge us?

160
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:28,700
抱歉 我们还在资本主义社会
'Scuse me. This is still a capitalist society.

161
00:10:28,700 --> 00:10:31,300
我以为Mickey是你的朋友
I thought Mickey was your mate.

162
00:10:31,300 --> 00:10:33,420
实际上 他就熟那么一丁点儿
Well, he's more of an acquaintance, really.

163
00:10:33,420 --> 00:10:36,340
不过 我愿意给你们打个折
But that said, I'm willing to make a discount.

164
00:10:36,340 --> 00:10:37,540
要多少?
How much?

165
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:38,980
你看着给
Call it a nifty.

166
00:10:44,260 --> 00:10:46,300
好
OK.

167
00:10:46,300 --> 00:10:48,620
我不知道它们是否有联系
I can't tell if these things are related,

168
00:10:48,620 --> 00:10:50,940
但毕加索被盗的前一天
but the day before the Picasso was nicked,

169
00:10:50,940 --> 00:10:52,420
飞来壮实的苏格兰佬
a hardcore jock crew flew in.

170
00:10:53,420 --> 00:10:54,620
苏格兰人?
Scottish?

171
00:10:54,620 --> 00:10:58,340
是McCrary兄弟 他们在西桥街借了套房子
The McCrary brothers. They took over a house in Westbridge Grove.

172
00:10:58,340 --> 00:11:02,540
目前 我只知道他们受人的指示行窃
Now, all I know about'em is that they nick to order,

173
00:11:02,540 --> 00:11:04,940
什么都行 通常是高档货
anything you like, usually upmarket.

174
00:11:04,940 --> 00:11:07,420
油画 汽车 古玩...
Paintings, cars, antiques...

175
00:11:07,420 --> 00:11:09,980
我是说 也许他们来这儿是有别的目的 但是...
I mean they could be here for something else, but...

176
00:11:11,380 --> 00:11:14,060
值得怀疑 不是吗?
It's worth asking the question, innit?

177
00:11:25,380 --> 00:11:26,670
好了 你有什么计划?
OK. What do you think?

178
00:11:26,670 --> 00:11:29,020
唔 我们可以敲敲门 说"呀 哎 宝贝"
Well, we could knock on the door, say "Och, aye, the noo,"

179
00:11:29,020 --> 00:11:31,200
然后问问他们是不是刚偷了一幅毕加索
and ask 'em if they've just nicked a Picasso.

180
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:33,380
真够直接的 但我们都不知道他们的身份
It's direct. But as we don't know who they are,

181
00:11:33,380 --> 00:11:35,350
这样有点冒险
I think it's a little bit foolhardy.

182
00:11:35,350 --> 00:11:37,860
是的 我知道 我就喜欢这样
Yeah, I know, that's what I like about it.

183
00:11:39,380 --> 00:11:40,420
"是谁?"
'Who is it?'

184
00:11:40,420 --> 00:11:41,690
Ash Morgan
It's Ash Morgan,

185
00:11:41,690 --> 00:11:43,900
我要和你谈谈你们刚刚偷到的那幅毕加索
I need to talk to you about the Picasso you just nicked.

186
00:11:43,900 --> 00:11:45,620
你把脑袋里面是浆糊吗?
Have you lost your marbles?

187
00:11:45,620 --> 00:11:48,780
对啊 我们的时间不多 最坏又能怎么样?
Yeah. We haven't got much time. What's the worst that could happen?

188
00:11:48,780 --> 00:11:50,420
他们会杀了我们!
They could kill us!

189
00:11:50,420 --> 00:11:54,020
哦 那至少 Mickey会知道我们曾拼死相救
Yeah, well, then at least Mickey would know we died trying.

190
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:16,680
你们还真有胆
You've got some bottle.

191
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:18,960
对 是啊 我们不得不这样
Yeah, well, needs must, and all of that.

192
00:12:18,970 --> 00:12:20,340
好啊 那你们进来吧
Well, in you come, then.

193
00:12:20,340 --> 00:12:22,840
你真客气 但如果你无所谓的话
That's very kind, but if it's all the same to you,

194
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:24,350
我们还是呆在这儿吧
we'll stay out here.

195
00:12:24,350 --> 00:12:24,780
很公平
Fair play.

196
00:12:24,780 --> 00:12:25,640
事情是这样的
The trouble is,

197
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:28,100
我的一个好朋友被Petre Sava抓了
a very good friend of mine is being held by Petre Sava,

198
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:30,120
你就是从那家伙那儿偷的毕加索
the bloke you nicked the Picasso from.

199
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:32,420
说来话长 但现在他认为是我们偷了画
Now, it's a long story, but now he thinks we got it.

200
00:12:32,420 --> 00:12:33,440
他为什么这么想?
And why would he think that?

201
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:35,390
因为我们告诉他是我们干的
Because we told him we did.

202
00:12:35,390 --> 00:12:37,220
是的 我们当时想卖一幅赝品给他
Yeah. We were trying to sell him a fake.

203
00:12:37,220 --> 00:12:38,260
我们行骗为生
We're grifters.

204
00:12:38,260 --> 00:12:39,540
没错 我们是干这行的
Yeah. It's what we do.

205
00:12:39,540 --> 00:12:41,060
我们读到报道说毕加索被偷了
We read about the Picasso being nicked,

206
00:12:41,060 --> 00:12:43,940
所以我们伪造了一幅 卖给一个私人收藏家
so we had a copy made to sell to a private collector,

207
00:12:43,940 --> 00:12:45,540
那人要求不多
one who wouldn't ask too many questions.

208
00:12:45,540 --> 00:12:48,670
如果他们也读到它被偷 就会相信那是真品
If they'd read about it being stolen, they'd believe it was real.

209
00:12:48,670 --> 00:12:49,220
正是这样
Exactly.

210
00:12:49,220 --> 00:12:53,260
问题是 我们卖画的对象正是你偷画的对象
Trouble is, the collector we took it to was the one you'd nicked it from.

211
00:12:53,260 --> 00:12:55,820
你能想象得出他有多生气
Which he wasn't very happy about, as you can imagine.

212
00:12:55,820 --> 00:12:58,280
多感人的故事 我都快热泪盈眶了
It's a beautiful story, and I'm getting all misty-eyed,

213
00:12:58,290 --> 00:13:00,100
但这同我们有什么关系?
but what's this got to do with us?

214
00:13:00,100 --> 00:13:03,270
嗯 额...如果你给我们那幅真的毕加索
Well, err... If you give us the real Picasso,

215
00:13:03,270 --> 00:13:05,500
就是你从Sava那偷来的那幅
the one that you nicked from Sava,

216
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:07,780
我们就能把我们的朋友救回来了
we can go and get our mate back.

217
00:13:07,780 --> 00:13:10,410
好吧 先假设我们有这幅画
Well, let's just say that we had this painting,

218
00:13:10,410 --> 00:13:13,860
我并不是说我们真有 你明白的...
not that I'm saying that we do, you understand...

219
00:13:13,860 --> 00:13:15,870
但他是你们朋友 又不是我们的
But he's your friend, not ours.

220
00:13:15,870 --> 00:13:17,220
所以跟我们有何相干?
So what's in it for us?

221
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:22,900
额 说实话 我还没好好想过 你想要什么?
Well, to be honest, I haven't thought that bit through. What do you want?

222
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:24,420
什么都不想要
Don't want anything.

223
00:13:24,420 --> 00:13:25,170
我跟你说
I tell you what,

224
00:13:25,170 --> 00:13:28,060
我可以给你两万美元然后帮你再把画偷回来
20 grand and I'll nick it straight back for you.

225
00:13:28,060 --> 00:13:30,320
要知道 就冲着你这份绝对的厚颜无耻
You know, just for the sheer brass neck of you,

226
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:31,580
我有兴趣帮你摆脱困境
I'm tempted to help you out.

227
00:13:31,580 --> 00:13:35,340
我最爱骗子了 尤其是漂亮的骗子
And I do love a grifter. Especially a pretty one.

228
00:13:35,340 --> 00:13:36,680
但它已经不在这了
But it's already been moved on.

229
00:13:36,680 --> 00:13:39,380
-去哪了?  -哦 我不能告诉你
-Where?  -Oh, I can't tell you that.

230
00:13:39,380 --> 00:13:44,100
-你必须说  -Ash是吗?  -是的
-You have to.  -Ash, is it?  -Yeah.

231
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:46,380
Ash
Ash.

232
00:13:46,380 --> 00:13:47,860
我不能说 小崽子
I can't do it, son.

233
00:13:47,860 --> 00:13:50,260
我们辛苦了好些年才建立起的声誉
We've worked years to build up a reputation

234
00:13:50,260 --> 00:13:51,460
靠的是完全的谨慎
based on complete discretion.

235
00:13:51,460 --> 00:13:54,430
我不能为了两个骗子就将它毁了
I can't piss that up the wall for a couple of grifters.

236
00:13:54,430 --> 00:13:56,220
所以我是绝不会讲的
So my lips are sealed.

237
00:13:56,220 --> 00:14:00,560
好吧 如果我威胁要揍你呢?
All right, what about if I threatened to beat it out of you?

238
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:02,860
我很佩服这样的想法
Then I would respect that.

239
00:14:02,860 --> 00:14:06,380
我和我兄弟Neil会很好地进行自我防卫
And me and my brother Neil here, would defend ourselves as best we could,

240
00:14:06,380 --> 00:14:10,420
我们会把你的脑袋拽下来煮煮吃掉
by ripping your head from the rest of your body and eating it.

241
00:14:10,420 --> 00:14:12,940
很好 我就问问
Fair enough, just asking.

242
00:14:12,940 --> 00:14:16,220
过得愉快
You have a nice day.

243
00:14:28,340 --> 00:14:29,930
看起来我们又回到原点了
So, looks like we're back to square one.

244
00:14:29,930 --> 00:14:32,160
不 不完全是 现在我们知道是谁偷了它
No, not exactly, now we know who stole it.

245
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:33,540
没错 但不知道他们是为谁偷
Yeah, but not who for.

246
00:14:33,540 --> 00:14:35,170
我们还是不知道它在哪里
We still don't know where it is.

247
00:14:35,170 --> 00:14:37,140
警方那边有什么消息吗 Albert?
Any news from the Old Bill, Albert?

248
00:14:37,140 --> 00:14:39,050
似乎他们知道的还没有我们多
It seems we know more than they do.

249
00:14:39,050 --> 00:14:41,420
要是McCrary兄弟并没有把它交出去呢?
What if the McCrary brothers haven't delivered it yet?

250
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:44,660
我们可以监视那间屋子 等待他们的行动 对不?
We could just watch the house and wait for them to make a move, right?

251
00:14:44,660 --> 00:14:47,590
要是他们明天或者下周才交货呢?
What if they're delivering it tomorrow or next week?

252
00:14:47,590 --> 00:14:48,980
我们只剩下4小时了
We've only got four hours left.

253
00:14:48,980 --> 00:14:50,460
Petre Sava那边呢?
What about Petre Sava?

254
00:14:50,460 --> 00:14:53,860
对 像你说的 我的确有所发现
Well, I did some digging about, like you said.

255
00:14:53,860 --> 00:14:55,500
Mickey是对的 他是一名高端艺术品收藏家
Mickey was right about him being a high-end art collector.

256
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:58,540
他的私人收藏能同大多数欧洲美术馆相匹敌
His private collection would rival most European galleries.

257
00:14:58,540 --> 00:15:01,630
我们刚知道 伦敦有六家夜总会归他所有
The last we knew, he owned half a dozen nightclubs in London,

258
00:15:01,630 --> 00:15:02,940
所有他肯定有问题
so he was bound to be a bit dodgy.

259
00:15:02,940 --> 00:15:04,240
嗯 这是件好事
Well, that's a good thing.

260
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:06,020
没错 尤其是知道有什么问题
Yeah. Until you find out how dodgy.

261
00:15:06,020 --> 00:15:08,840
-贩卖人口...  -啊...
-Human trafficking...  -Aah...

262
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:09,780
一级毒品销售
Class A drug distribution,

263
00:15:09,780 --> 00:15:12,260
还有一个保护费勒索组织 发起于罗马尼亚
and a protection racket that started in Romania,

264
00:15:12,260 --> 00:15:15,700
现在已遍布八个欧洲城市
and has now spread over eight European cities.

265
00:15:15,700 --> 00:15:18,180
我们要把Mickey救出来
We need to get Mickey out of there.

266
00:15:30,620 --> 00:15:32,820
你把那个黑人怎么样了?
So what did you do with the black guy?

267
00:15:32,820 --> 00:15:34,900
他在我的汽车行李箱里
He's in the boot of my car.

268
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:37,860
-还能呼吸吗?  -当然
-Can he breathe?  -Sure.

269
00:15:37,860 --> 00:15:39,900
至少我觉得能
At least I think so.

270
00:15:43,340 --> 00:15:45,580
如果他们带不回我的画...
If they don't bring me my painting...

271
00:15:48,740 --> 00:15:50,320
..你认为我们是该杀了他
..you think we should kill him,

272
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:51,660
还是在他身上切下几块?
or just cut some bits off?

273
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:55,100
或者都干?
Or both?

274
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:57,940
都干
Both is good.

275
00:16:05,100 --> 00:16:09,940
要知道 在西方可不太切人
They don't cut people up too much in the West, you know.

276
00:16:09,940 --> 00:16:14,620
同样也不太杀人 他们"给点颜色"
They don't kill them very much, either. They "beat up".

277
00:16:14,620 --> 00:16:18,620
但如果你只是"给点颜色" 等他们养好了
But if you just "beat up," they get better,

278
00:16:18,620 --> 00:16:21,540
他们会找些朋友回来报复
they find some friends, and then they come back.

279
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:28,330
如果你切下几块肉寄给他们的朋友
If you cut bits off and post them to their friends,

280
00:16:28,330 --> 00:16:30,380
这类事就不会发生了
this doesn't happen.

281
00:16:30,380 --> 00:16:33,740
不会 这有效得多
No. It's more efficient.

282
00:16:33,740 --> 00:16:35,260
没错
Exactly.

283
00:16:36,820 --> 00:16:39,580
所以 两件事我们都干
So, both it is.

284
00:16:39,580 --> 00:16:40,660
你切...
You cut...

285
00:16:43,260 --> 00:16:44,380
..我杀
..I kill.

286
00:17:20,380 --> 00:17:22,110
Mickey在哪?
Where's Mickey?

287
00:17:22,120 --> 00:17:24,260
他被一罗马尼亚匪徒绑架了
He's being held hostage by a Romanian gangster

288
00:17:24,260 --> 00:17:26,640
除非我们找到一幅画着花园小猫的画
who won't release him

289
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:27,620
他是不会放人的
until we find a painting of a cat in a garden.

290
00:17:27,620 --> 00:17:28,940
对 没错 是的
Yeah, right, yeah.

291
00:17:32,140 --> 00:17:34,060
你们这群人可真逗
You crack me up, you lot.

292
00:17:34,060 --> 00:17:36,870
多生动的想象力 像我妈过去常说的那样
Very vivid imaginations, as my mum used to say.

293
00:17:36,870 --> 00:17:39,100
听着 你们的行当里也许需要这个
Mind you, you probably need them in your line of work.

294
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:40,670
干杯 Eddie
Cheers, Eddie.

295
00:17:40,670 --> 00:17:42,780
听着 给我们几分钟好吗?我们在思考
Look, give us a couple of minutes, will you? We're thinking.

296
00:17:42,780 --> 00:17:46,500
我以为我能听听呢 哦 你有个电话
I thought I could hear something. Oh, you had a phone call.

297
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:47,670
一位女士...Molly?
Nice lady... Molly?

298
00:17:47,670 --> 00:17:49,060
-Dolly  -Dolly 就是她
-Dolly.  -Dolly. That's it.

299
00:17:49,060 --> 00:17:50,790
她说她知道你们想要什么了
She said she's got what you want,

300
00:17:50,790 --> 00:17:53,540
不过你必须把小可爱送过去 反正就这意思
only you have to send the cute one, whatever that means.

301
00:17:55,860 --> 00:17:57,820
没门
No way.

302
00:17:57,820 --> 00:17:59,900
哦...这不行
Oh... No way.

303
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:00,860
想都别想!
No way!

304
00:18:03,940 --> 00:18:05,700
不...
No...

305
00:18:05,700 --> 00:18:06,780
..行
..way.

306
00:18:09,580 --> 00:18:11,460
来啦!
Ta-daa!

307
00:18:18,020 --> 00:18:20,340
我不知道你喜欢红酒还是白酒
I didn't know if you liked red or white,

308
00:18:20,340 --> 00:18:23,020
所以都拿来了 噢
so I brought one of each. Oh.

309
00:18:23,020 --> 00:18:26,380
哈哈...
Ha-ha...

310
00:18:42,060 --> 00:18:43,580
好可怕
It was horrible.

311
00:18:43,580 --> 00:18:48,060
-哦 你被迫做了什么?  -我不想说 
-So, did you actually have to? -I don't want to talk about it.

312
00:18:48,060 --> 00:18:49,940
哦...
Oh...

313
00:18:49,940 --> 00:18:51,860
不 当然不用
No, of course not.

314
00:19:02,220 --> 00:19:03,460
她掏出了她的假牙
She took her teeth out.

315
00:19:07,700 --> 00:19:09,980
那么 她究竟说了什么?
So, did she say anything at all?

316
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:14,060
深呼吸 Sean
Take a deep breath, Sean.

317
00:19:15,100 --> 00:19:18,020
也许有助于你忘掉那些画面
It might help to make the pictures go away.

318
00:19:24,780 --> 00:19:27,550
Petre Sava在肯辛通的一场拍卖会上
Petre Sava bought A Small Cat In The Garden by Picasso

319
00:19:27,550 --> 00:19:29,540
买下了毕加索的《花园里的小猫》
at an auction in Kensington.

320
00:19:29,540 --> 00:19:32,820
他的出价高于一个名为Matthew Fairchild的私人收藏家
He outbid a private collector called Matthew Fairchild,

321
00:19:32,830 --> 00:19:33,700
他是一名投资银行家
who's an investment banker,

322
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:36,300
恰巧是Louise Fairchild的父亲
and happens to be the father of Louise Fairchild,

323
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:37,780
结婚改姓前她姓Holmes
whose married name is Holmes.

324
00:19:37,780 --> 00:19:38,860
我们认识吗?
Should we know her?

325
00:19:38,860 --> 00:19:40,300
不 但你们也许听说过她丈夫
No, but you might've heard of her husband.

326
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:43,180
-Harry Holmes!  -那个Harry Holmes?
-Harry Holmes!  -THE Harry Holmes?

327
00:19:43,180 --> 00:19:44,860
恐怕是的
'Fraid so.

328
00:20:12,340 --> 00:20:16,100
没事 没事的 冷静点 冷静
It's all right. It's all right, calm down. Calm down.

329
00:20:17,420 --> 00:20:21,020
现在 我知道你不是软柿子...
Now, I understand you're not a grass...

330
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:25,660
..我的确很欣赏男人的这种气魄 真的
..and I admire that in a man, I really do.

331
00:20:28,300 --> 00:20:30,700
我要你自己来切开
I need you to open up for me.

332
00:20:31,860 --> 00:20:34,980
不然...就我来
One way...or another.

333
00:20:36,140 --> 00:20:37,970
当Harry Holmes发现
When Harry Holmes found out

334
00:20:37,970 --> 00:20:40,660
是Petre Sava在油画竞拍中赢了他岳父
it was Petre Sava who beat his father-in-law to the painting,

335
00:20:40,660 --> 00:20:42,940
他很生气 我敢说 这有些伤了他的骄傲
he wasn't happy. It hurt his pride a bit. I bet.

336
00:20:42,940 --> 00:20:46,820
我听说他像狗一样 借着结婚的机会混入了上流社会
I heard he was like a dog with two whatsits when he married into the upper classes.

337
00:20:46,820 --> 00:20:49,310
他向来喜欢对打猎 射击 垂钓
He's always fancied hunting, shooting and fishing.

