00:42:09,500 --> 00:42:10,260
这个计划可行
Sounds like a plan.

682
00:42:10,260 --> 00:42:11,940
好吧 首先我得先喝一杯
Yeah, well, first, I need a drink.

683
00:42:17,580 --> 00:42:18,700
拿酒来
Set 'em up.

684
00:42:20,380 --> 00:42:21,900
你们来了!
There you are!

685
00:42:30,300 --> 00:42:33,460
疯子Dolly告诉我们在哪里能找到你们
Mad Dolly told us where to find you.

686
00:42:33,460 --> 00:42:34,620
哦?
Oh?

687
00:42:34,620 --> 00:42:37,140
在宾馆里的是你吧 是不是?
That was you at the hotel, wasn't it?

688
00:42:37,140 --> 00:42:38,220
宾馆?
Hotel?

689
00:42:38,220 --> 00:42:39,260
我看见你离开的
I saw you leaving.

690
00:42:40,860 --> 00:42:42,740
你们是正好经过吗?
Just passing, were you?

691
00:42:42,740 --> 00:42:45,220
没错 是的 我们 额...
That's right, yeah, we erm...

692
00:42:45,220 --> 00:42:47,460
我们知道了你们在哪里
Well, we found out where you were

693
00:42:47,460 --> 00:42:51,580
我们想再试一次 你懂得 试图说服你们...
and we thought we'd try again, you know, to convince you to...

694
00:42:51,580 --> 00:42:54,140
让我们把画带走
let us take the painting.

695
00:42:54,140 --> 00:42:56,340
我也是这么想的
That's what I thought.

696
00:42:56,340 --> 00:43:00,100
也就是说是你们触响了警铃 是不是?
So it was you guys that set off the alarm, was it?

697
00:43:00,100 --> 00:43:01,520
是啊 是 我们...
Yeah, yeah, we...

698
00:43:01,520 --> 00:43:02,540
我跟你们说的没错吧?
What did I tell you?

699
00:43:06,580 --> 00:43:09,500
所以我们到这来 想要谢谢你们的!
That's why we're here, we wanted to say thank you!

700
00:43:10,660 --> 00:43:12,620
哦?
Eh?

701
00:43:13,620 --> 00:43:16,700
听着 我不知道你们为什么要那么做 去触发警铃
Look, I don't know why you hit the alarm when you did,

702
00:43:16,700 --> 00:43:18,350
但是如果你们没那么做的话
but if you hadn't,

703
00:43:18,350 --> 00:43:19,300
我们就还在那里得意
we'd have just waltzed up there

704
00:43:19,300 --> 00:43:21,020
而Harry Holmes在我们房里
and found Harry Holmes in our room.

705
00:43:21,020 --> 00:43:24,420
噢 是的 不要客气 
Yeah, well, you know, don't mention it.

706
00:43:24,420 --> 00:43:26,020
到底发生了什么事?
So what happened?

707
00:43:26,020 --> 00:43:27,100
你找到了我们
You found us

708
00:43:27,100 --> 00:43:30,500
然后看见Harry和他那伙人也在那 对不对?
and then you saw Harry and his goons there too, right?

709
00:43:30,500 --> 00:43:32,910
对的 是 于是... 我们就赶快逃走
That's right, yeah. So...we legged it.

710
00:43:32,910 --> 00:43:34,780
但是我们不想丢下你们不管...
Only we didn't want to drop you in it, so...

711
00:43:34,780 --> 00:43:35,660
所以就触动了警铃
So we hit the alarm.

712
00:43:38,180 --> 00:43:41,740
我只知道要不是你们 我们就完蛋了
Look. All I know is if it wasn't for you guys we would be screwed.

713
00:43:41,740 --> 00:43:43,900
所以 真的很感谢你们
So, thank you.

714
00:43:43,900 --> 00:43:46,340
别客气 我希望你们也会为我们这么做
It's a pleasure, I hope you'd do the same for us.

715
00:43:46,340 --> 00:43:47,660
噢 那当然!
Oh, absolutely!

716
00:43:47,660 --> 00:43:48,860
好吧 这边请
Well, there you go.

717
00:43:48,860 --> 00:43:50,780
我们很想留下来跟你们一起喝杯啤酒
We'd love to stay and have a beer with you,

718
00:43:50,780 --> 00:43:52,500
但是我们要去赶飞机
but we have a flight to catch.

719
00:43:52,500 --> 00:43:55,540
我们要回家 开始花这笔钱了
We've got to get home and make a start on spending this.

720
00:44:01,100 --> 00:44:04,660
四十万... 这幅画
400 grand...for the painting.

721
00:44:04,660 --> 00:44:06,820
画?
The painting?

722
00:44:06,820 --> 00:44:08,220
毕加索的
The Picasso.

723
00:44:10,220 --> 00:44:12,740
我们卖给Harry一幅Dolly的伪造品
We sold Harry one of the duds Dolly made.

724
00:44:12,740 --> 00:44:15,410
是啊 我听说了 所以他在找你们
Yeah, I heard. That's why he was looking for you.

725
00:44:15,410 --> 00:44:16,260
哦 那还用说
Oh, no doubt.

726
00:44:16,260 --> 00:44:19,070
但是我们还有另外一个买主等候买一幅真品
But we also had another buyer lined up for the real one.

727
00:44:19,070 --> 00:44:19,780
一个德国佬
German guy.

728
00:44:22,820 --> 00:44:24,040
等一下
Wait.

729
00:44:24,040 --> 00:44:30,140
你说你将"其中一幅赝品"卖给Harry?
You said you sold "one of the duds" to Harry?

730
00:44:31,940 --> 00:44:34,540
你还卖了一幅伪造品给德国人?
So you sold a dud to the German too?

731
00:44:34,540 --> 00:44:40,380
不是的 他拿到的是真品 他出价最高的
No, no, he got the real thing. Bid the highest you see.

732
00:44:40,380 --> 00:44:42,790
不是 我们让Dolly画了两幅赝品
No, we had Dolly make two duds.

733
00:44:42,790 --> 00:44:44,540
其中的一幅卖给了Harry
We sold one to Harry,

734
00:44:44,540 --> 00:44:48,020
另外一幅我们准备卖给一个在宾馆酒吧的澳洲家伙
and the other we were going to sell to some Aussie guy in the hotel bar,

735
00:44:48,030 --> 00:44:48,940
可是他没出现
but he was a no show.

736
00:44:48,940 --> 00:44:51,740
是吗 但是你不可能已经把真的卖掉了
Yeah, yeah, but you can't have sold the real one,

737
00:44:51,740 --> 00:44:54,820
因为Harry发现它在你们的房间里
because Harry found it in your room.

738
00:44:54,820 --> 00:44:57,700
那他回到家肯定要大失所望了
He would have been pretty disappointed when he got home.

739
00:44:57,700 --> 00:45:00,420
-呃?  -我们今天下午就跟这个德国家伙成交了
Eh? Did the deal with the German guy this afternoon,

740
00:45:00,420 --> 00:45:02,260
比Harry找到我们要早很多
long before Harry found us.

741
00:45:02,260 --> 00:45:05,100
如果他在我们房间里看到那幅画 那是另一幅仿造品
If he found a painting in our room, it was the other dud.

742
00:45:05,100 --> 00:45:07,500
糟了 我想起来我们把它挂墙上了
Shit, I think we actually hung it up on the wall.

743
00:45:07,500 --> 00:45:10,300
我们把它留在那儿 当做给宾馆的一点小礼物
We were leaving it as a wee present for the hotel.

744
00:45:10,300 --> 00:45:15,180
听着 我说过了 我们来就是要谢谢你们
Look, like I said, we just came here to say thank you.

745
00:45:19,180 --> 00:45:22,940
哦 顺便问一下 你们朋友的事情进行的怎么样?
Oh, by the way, how did, er... How did things pan out with your friend?

746
00:45:22,940 --> 00:45:25,820
噢 我们... 我们还在进行当中
Oh, well, we're, er...We're still working on it.

747
00:45:25,820 --> 00:45:27,940
好吧 祝你们顺利
Well, good luck with that.

748
00:45:27,940 --> 00:45:29,500
加油
Cheers.

749
00:45:39,460 --> 00:45:41,260
就是说 我们偷了另一幅赝品?
So we stole another fake?

750
00:45:41,260 --> 00:45:43,970
你告诉Sava我们有半小时
You told Sava we had half an hour.

751
00:45:43,970 --> 00:45:45,500
我们只有十五分钟了
We've got 15 minutes.

752
00:45:48,660 --> 00:45:49,860
现在怎么办?
So what do we do now?

753
00:45:51,380 --> 00:45:53,420
给你 伙计
Here you are, mate.

754
00:46:21,940 --> 00:46:26,380
当你置身于法律之外 游走在社会边缘
When you live outside the law, on the fringes of society,

755
00:46:26,380 --> 00:46:30,100
你总是会碰到这样的日子
you're always going to have days like this.

756
00:46:30,100 --> 00:46:32,820
你称之为办公室里糟糕的一天
What you might call a bad day in the office.

757
00:46:34,940 --> 00:46:37,500
最重要的是不要慌
Well, the thing is not to panic.

758
00:46:37,500 --> 00:46:42,020
因为那种人 像猎狗一样 
Because people like this lot, they're like dogs,

759
00:46:42,020 --> 00:46:43,860
他们能嗅到恐惧
they can smell fear.

760
00:46:45,700 --> 00:46:49,500
所以对策就是让他们以为 你知道些他们不知道的事
So the trick is to make them think you know something they don't.

761
00:46:49,500 --> 00:46:52,820
这样一来在他们还没搞清楚怎么回事之前
That way they'll generally hold off killing you

762
00:46:52,820 --> 00:46:55,100
他们就不会急着杀了你
while they try and work out what it is.

763
00:47:08,460 --> 00:47:10,220
画带来了吗?
You have brought my painting?

764
00:47:10,220 --> 00:47:12,180
-你把我的朋友带来了吗?  -先看画
-You brought my friend?  -Painting first.

765
00:47:12,180 --> 00:47:14,390
先把朋友交给我们 否则没什么好谈的
Friend first or there's no deal.

766
00:47:14,390 --> 00:47:16,500
我想你们这种处境没资格讨价还价 是不是?
I don't think you're in a position to negotiate, do you?

767
00:47:16,500 --> 00:47:19,700
如果你这么认为 那你就大错特错了
If you believe that, it could be the worst mistake you ever made.

768
00:47:19,700 --> 00:47:24,620
我见我的朋友...然后你看你的画
I see my friend...you see your painting.

769
00:47:47,300 --> 00:47:48,740
轮到你了
Now your turn.

770
00:48:17,980 --> 00:48:21,380
好吧 我的画在哪里?
Right. Who's got my painting?

771
00:48:21,380 --> 00:48:23,420
这不关你的事 Harry
This is none of your business, Harry.

772
00:48:23,420 --> 00:48:25,220
那我就让它关我的事 Boris
Well, I'm making it my business, Boris,

773
00:48:25,220 --> 00:48:27,820
这么久以来 我一直围着你团团转
I've been dancing around you lot for too long.

774
00:48:27,820 --> 00:48:29,620
我不叫Boris
My name is not Boris.

775
00:48:29,620 --> 00:48:31,300
我说你是你就是
It is when I'm talking to you.

776
00:48:31,300 --> 00:48:33,980
你知道 叫我Boris是一种种族歧视
You know, calling me Boris is racist.

777
00:48:33,980 --> 00:48:35,180
算你倒霉
Tough.

778
00:48:35,180 --> 00:48:38,340
呃... 对不起 我们可以继续我们的事吗?
Er, excuse me, can we, er...Can we get on with this, please?

779
00:48:38,340 --> 00:48:40,200
这儿有你什么事儿?
What are you doing here?

780
00:48:40,200 --> 00:48:42,060
你以为我干嘛来这儿出风头?
What do you think I'm flaming doing here?

781
00:48:42,060 --> 00:48:44,940
我是来交易这幅画的...
I've come to swap this painting...

782
00:48:44,940 --> 00:48:46,460
替同伴来的
for my mate.

783
00:48:46,460 --> 00:48:50,020
-这是我的画  -非也 是我的才对
-That is my painting.  -No. My painting.

784
00:48:50,020 --> 00:48:53,020
-我正大光明搞来的  -现在我要拿回来
-I nicked it, fair and square.  -And now I'm getting it back.

785
00:48:53,020 --> 00:48:54,660
有完没完!
That's enough!

786
00:48:56,340 --> 00:48:59,740
-你丫吼谁呢?  -吼你!
-Who you shouting at? You!

787
00:48:59,740 --> 00:49:01,420
你们俩！
The pair of you!

788
00:49:02,460 --> 00:49:05,860
你们有听说过什么叫盗亦有道吗?
Have you never heard of honour amongst thieves?

789
00:49:05,860 --> 00:49:09,820
你们同行间没有过点头称赞的欣赏吗?
Some kind of nodding appreciation amongst your peers?

790
00:49:12,460 --> 00:49:15,260
你们还没断奶啊
You're like a couple of five-year-olds.

791
00:49:15,260 --> 00:49:19,420
"小姐 拜托了 他抢我的画" 多可悲
"Please, Miss, he's nicked my painting." It's pathetic.

792
00:49:19,420 --> 00:49:22,980
-我受够你们俩了!  -拿画呀
-And I've had it with both of you!  -Get the painting.

793
00:49:22,980 --> 00:49:24,500
啊 啊 啊!
Ah, ah, ah!

794
00:49:32,780 --> 00:49:35,350
子弹曾刷刷的从我眼前飞过
I've had a gun shoved up me hooter,

795
00:49:35,350 --> 00:49:36,740
我还被倒吊起来
been hung upside down

796
00:49:36,740 --> 00:49:38,500
还被踢到半空去过
and kicked up in the air.

797
00:49:38,500 --> 00:49:42,340
我跑遍半个伦敦的途中 被3个国籍的势力威胁过
I've been threatened by at least three nationalities

798
00:49:42,340 --> 00:49:47,140
就为了这幅破画 画的是某个后院里有只小猫
while running around half of London chasing some stupid picture of a cat in someone's back garden

799
00:49:47,140 --> 00:49:52,100
看上去就像个糖吃多了的3岁小孩的信手涂鸦
that looks like it was done by a three-year-old on a sugar rush.

800
00:49:52,100 --> 00:49:57,660
我被骗过 蒙过 还被老是被骂
I've been lied to, cheated and generally abused

801
00:49:57,660 --> 00:50:00,940
就是因为我和这几个同伴想要赚个童叟无欺的名声
just because me and my mate here were trying to earn an honest crust

802
00:50:00,940 --> 00:50:03,380
而这个Rasputin却神经到绑架了他
when Rasputin here went and kidnapped him.

803
00:50:03,380 --> 00:50:06,770
喂 Rasputin还不如Boris好呢
Hey. Rasputin is worse than Boris.

804
00:50:06,770 --> 00:50:07,700
我说了 闭嘴!
I said, shut it!

805
00:50:08,980 --> 00:50:13,700
现在我不知道谁画该给谁了 说实话
Now, I don't know whose painting this is and, to be quite honest,I don't give a flying toss!

806
00:50:13,700 --> 00:50:15,360
我今天过得很糟糕!
I've had a very bad day!

807
00:50:15,360 --> 00:50:16,780
你知道你在和谁说话么?
Do you know who you're talking to?

808
00:50:17,820 --> 00:50:19,700
管他是谁
Never mind who I'm talking to.

809
00:50:21,540 --> 00:50:25,560
你该担心的是我们是什么人物 小子
You ought to worry about who we are, son.

810
00:50:25,560 --> 00:50:27,220
咱是骗子 哦耶
We're grifters. Yeah.

811
00:50:29,380 --> 00:50:33,020
站这的这家伙 埃菲尔铁塔是他卖的
This bloke over here. He's sold the Eiffel Tower,

812
00:50:33,020 --> 00:50:36,540
威斯敏斯特宫和悉尼歌剧院也是
the Palace Of Westminster and the Sydney Opera House.

813
00:50:36,540 --> 00:50:39,100
我们让银行破产 搞垮企业 收拾政党
We broke banks, companies and political parties.

814
00:50:39,100 --> 00:50:41,860
我们欺负拉斯维加斯黑手党
We took on the mafia in Las Vegas

815
00:50:41,860 --> 00:50:45,900
还把伦敦政治保安处整得像一群饭桶
and we made the London Special Branch look like the Keystone Cops.

816
00:50:45,900 --> 00:50:49,020
还想吓唬我们?省省吧!
So never mind about you two threatening us!

817
00:50:51,340 --> 00:50:54,380
现在是我在威胁你们!
Now, I'm threatening you!

818
00:50:57,460 --> 00:51:00,700
我们会拿你们作消遣
We're going to make you our hobby.

819
00:51:00,700 --> 00:51:06,100
花几个通宵 想办法把你们榨干 把你们掏空
Spend sleepless nights working out how to take away everything from you, every penny.

820
00:51:06,100 --> 00:51:09,300
你要担心的远不止这副该死的狗屁画
It won't be just a sodding painting you have to worry about,

821
00:51:09,300 --> 00:51:12,580
好好盘算晚上要在哪儿落脚吧
you'll be working out where you're going to sleep at night.

822
00:51:16,820 --> 00:51:20,700
因为我们要把你们给掏干净了
Because we're going to pick you clean.

823
00:51:20,700 --> 00:51:24,340
我们会把你们骨头上的肉剔个精光
We'll strip every bit of flesh off the bone.

824
00:51:37,900 --> 00:51:40,700
说得好 我就一个问题
Nice speech. I got just one question.

825
00:51:40,700 --> 00:51:42,180
嗯 说?
Yeah, what's that?

826
00:51:43,860 --> 00:51:46,860
你们这群家伙要是死了 还怎么做事呢?
How are you lot going to do that, when you're dead?

827
00:51:46,860 --> 00:51:48,940
很好
Very good.

828
00:51:52,260 --> 00:51:53,820
现在 把我的画给我
Now, give me my painting.

829
00:51:53,820 --> 00:51:57,860
不 不 把我的画给我才是
No. No. You give me MY painting.

830
00:52:01,820 --> 00:52:05,700
有些人就是不听话 对吧?
Some people never listen, do they?

831
00:52:05,700 --> 00:52:08,180
跟你们讲...
I tell you what...

832
00:52:08,180 --> 00:52:10,460
你们自己解决
you can sort it out amongst yourselves.

833
00:52:46,980 --> 00:52:50,860
把它踢到旁边去! 嗯 就是这样
Get it round the side! Yeah, that's it.

834
00:52:51,940 --> 00:52:53,860
瞧你在干嘛!
Watch what you're doing!

835
00:52:55,620 --> 00:52:57,660
别伤到画!
Don't damage it!

836
00:52:57,660 --> 00:53:01,100
电话也不来个 手信也没有
You didn't phone, you didn't write.

837
00:53:01,100 --> 00:53:03,060
对不起啦 我一直束手束脚的
Sorry, mate, I've been a bit tied up.

838
00:53:05,100 --> 00:53:07,380
是那谁吗?
Is that who I think it is?

839
00:53:07,380 --> 00:53:09,820
嗯 Harry Holmes
Harry Holmes, yeah.

840
00:53:09,820 --> 00:53:11,700
还好他出现了
Good job he turned up.

841
00:53:11,700 --> 00:53:14,580
嗯 额...我打给他的
Yeah, well...I phoned him.

842
00:53:15,820 --> 00:53:18,220
-你打给他?  -嗯
-You phoned him?  -Yeah.

843
00:53:18,220 --> 00:53:19,660
那我们现在干嘛?
So what do we do now?

844
00:53:26,980 --> 00:53:29,060
喂 Harry?
Hello. Harry?

845
00:53:29,060 --> 00:53:33,980
你想鸡道McCrary兄弟瞒着你干了咩勾当吗?
Would you be interested to know who the McCrary boys were working for when they double-crossed you?

846
00:53:33,980 --> 00:53:36,580
系啊 我鸡道啊 你有笔吗?
Aye, I do know. Have you got a pen?

847
00:53:39,900 --> 00:53:42,140
看好画啊 行不行啊?
Just watch the painting, will ya?

848
